ture\", \"from\": 1159, \"to\": 1166}, {\"ngram\": \"the company\", \"from\": 1194, \"to\": 1205}, {\"ngram\": \"the founder\", \"from\": 1280, \"to\": 1291}, {\"ngram\": \"the modern Games\", \"from\": 1335, \"to\": 1351}, {\"ngram\": \"art competitions\", \"from\": 1357, \"to\": 1373}, {\"ngram\": \"his vision\", \"from\": 1389, \"to\": 1399}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games\", \"from\": 1403, \"to\": 1420}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Deprived of the aura of the Arts contests,\\\" he oncedeclared, \\\"Olympic Games are only World Championships\\\" Starting from theStockholm Olympic Games in 1912, architects, sculptors, poets and painters took part in competitions for their arts.\", \"from\": 1423, \"to\": 1663, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the aura\", \"from\": 1436, \"to\": 1444}, {\"ngram\": \"the Arts contests\", \"from\": 1448, \"to\": 1465}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic Games\", \"from\": 1486, \"to\": 1499}, {\"ngram\": \"only World Championships\", \"from\": 1504, \"to\": 1528}, {\"ngram\": \"theStockholm Olympic Games\", \"from\": 1544, \"to\": 1570}, {\"ngram\": \"architects\", \"from\": 1580, \"to\": 1590}, {\"ngram\": \"sculptors\", \"from\": 1592, \"to\": 1601}, {\"ngram\": \"poets\", \"from\": 1603, \"to\": 1608}, {\"ngram\": \"painters\", \"from\": 1613, \"to\": 1621}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 1627, \"to\": 1631}, {\"ngram\": \"competitions\", \"from\": 1635, \"to\": 1647}, {\"ngram\": \"their arts\", \"from\": 1652, \"to\": 1662}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Unlike the sporting categories which were limited to amateur athletes, professionals were permitted to enter.\", \"from\": 1665, \"to\": 1774, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the sporting categories\", \"from\": 1672, \"to\": 1695}, {\"ngram\": \"amateur athletes\", \"from\": 1718, \"to\": 1734}, {\"ngram\": \"professionals\", \"from\": 1736, \"to\": 1749}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One condition was that they were to be original works and were to be inspired by the concept of sport.\", \"from\": 1775, \"to\": 1877, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"One condition\", \"from\": 1775, \"to\": 1788}, {\"ngram\": \"original works\", \"from\": 1814, \"to\": 1828}, {\"ngram\": \"the concept\", \"from\": 1856, \"to\": 1867}, {\"ngram\": \"sport\", \"from\": 1871, \"to\": 1876}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In addition, the jury could only consider works not previously published, exhibited, or performed and would not be accepted if they had been exhibited prior to the Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 1878, \"to\": 2056, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"addition\", \"from\": 1881, \"to\": 1889}, {\"ngram\": \"the jury\", \"from\": 1891, \"to\": 1899}, {\"ngram\": \"works\", \"from\": 1920, \"to\": 1925}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games\", \"from\": 2038, \"to\": 2055}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The format of the arts competitions wasinconsistentand occasionallychaotic: a category might garner a silver medal, but no gold, or the jury might be so disappointed in the submissions that it awarded no medals at all.\", \"from\": 2057, \"to\": 2275, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The format\", \"from\": 2057, \"to\": 2067}, {\"ngram\": \"the arts competitions\", \"from\": 2071, \"to\": 2092}, {\"ngram\": \"a category\", \"from\": 2133, \"to\": 2143}, {\"ngram\": \"a silver medal\", \"from\": 2157, \"to\": 2171}, {\"ngram\": \"no gold\", \"from\": 2177, \"to\": 2184}, {\"ngram\": \"the jury\", \"from\": 2189, \"to\": 2197}, {\"ngram\": \"the submissions\", \"from\": 2226, \"to\": 2241}, {\"ngram\": \"no medals\", \"from\": 2258, \"to\": 2267}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ireland's entries were from many well-known creatives.\", \"from\": 2277, \"to\": 2331, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2277, \"end\": 2284, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9999998730172673, \"rank\": 1.2698292772919943e-07, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_I