 5365}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Many of the recorded names of artists and artworks werewrong or incorrect, descriptions of the artworks were vague or absent and artists sometimes created multiple works with similar titles.\", \"from\": 5396, \"to\": 5586, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the recorded names\", \"from\": 5404, \"to\": 5422}, {\"ngram\": \"artists\", \"from\": 5426, \"to\": 5433}, {\"ngram\": \"artworks\", \"from\": 5438, \"to\": 5446}, {\"ngram\": \"descriptions\", \"from\": 5471, \"to\": 5483}, {\"ngram\": \"the artworks\", \"from\": 5487, \"to\": 5499}, {\"ngram\": \"artists\", \"from\": 5525, \"to\": 5532}, {\"ngram\": \"multiple works\", \"from\": 5551, \"to\": 5565}, {\"ngram\": \"similar titles\", \"from\": 5571, \"to\": 5585}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With only a small number of the artworks ever photographed, they are close to impossible to track down.\", \"from\": 5587, \"to\": 5690, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"only a small number\", \"from\": 5592, \"to\": 5611}, {\"ngram\": \"the artworks\", \"from\": 5615, \"to\": 5627}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hamilton's bronze would be Ireland's last medal in the arts categories as the cultural aspects of the Olympic Games were no longer in competition format.\", \"from\": 5692, \"to\": 5845, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5692, \"end\": 5700, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hamilton_Academical_F.C.\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.215660832705329e-24, \"text\": \"Hamilton\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hamilton_Academical_F.C.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hamilton_Academical_F.C.\"}, {\"begin\": 5719, \"end\": 5726, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9999998730172673, \"rank\": 1.2698292772919943e-07, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the arts categories\", \"from\": 5743, \"to\": 5762}, {\"ngram\": \"the cultural aspects\", \"from\": 5766, \"to\": 5786}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games\", \"from\": 5790, \"to\": 5807}, {\"ngram\": \"competition format\", \"from\": 5826, \"to\": 5844}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After de Coubertin's death, the new president of the International Olympic Committee led a campaign against the arts and they were cancelled by the time the1952 Olympicswere held in Helsinki.\", \"from\": 5846, \"to\": 6037, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5899, \"end\": 5930, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 6028, \"end\": 6036, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Helsinki\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.869623095505436e-14, \"text\": \"Helsinki\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Helsinki\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Helsinki\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"de Coubertin's death\", \"from\": 5852, \"to\": 5872}, {\"ngram\": \"the new president\", \"from\": 5874, \"to\": 5891}, {\"ngram\": \"a campaign\", \"from\": 5935, \"to\": 5945}, {\"ngram\": \"the arts\", \"from\": 5954, \"to\": 5962}, {\"ngram\": \"the time\", \"from\": 5990, \"to\": 5998}, {\"ngram\": \"the1952 Olympicswere\", \"from\": 5999, \"to\": 6019}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead, they were replaced by a non-competitive exhibition to occur during the Games, which eventually became known as theCultural Olympia, which still runs today.\", \"from\": 6038, \"to\": 6202, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a non-competitive exhibition\", \"from\": 6069, \"to\": 6097}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 6114, \"to\": 6123}, {\"ngram\": \"theCultural Olympia\", \"from\": 6158, \"to\": 6177}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The main reason for the scrapping of the arts categories was not because of a lack of interest, but because most of the entrants were professionals which conflicted with the amateur ethos of the Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 6204, \"to\": 6413, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The main reason\", \"from\": 6204, \"to\": 6219}, {\"ngram\": \"the scrapping\", \"from\": 6224, \"to\": 6237}, {\"ngram\": \"the arts categories\", \"from\": 6241, \"to\": 6260}, {\"ngram\": \"a lack\", \"from\": 6280, \"to\": 6286}, {\"ngram\": \"interest\", \"from\": 6290, \"to\": 6298}, {\"ngram\": \"the entrants\", \"from\": 6320, \"to\": 6332}, {\"ngram\": \"professionals\", \"from\": 6338, \"to\": 6351}, {\"ngram\": \"the amateur ethos\", \"from\": 6374, \"to\": 6391}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games\", \"from\": 6395, \"to\": 6412}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a report on the state of the Olympics, the IOCdeemedthat \\\"since art competition contestants are practically all professionals, Olympic medals should not be awarded.\", \"from\": 6414, \"to\": 6581, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a report\", \"from\": 6417, \"to\": 6425}, {\"ngram\": \"the state\", \"from\": 6429, \"to\": 6438}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 6442, \"to\": 6454}, {\"ngram\": \"the IOCdeemedthat\", \"from\": 6456, \"to\": 6473}, {\"ngram\": \"art competition contestants\", \"from\": 6481, \"to\": 6508}, {\"ngram\": \"practically all professionals\", \"from\": 6513, \"to\": 6542}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic medals\", \"from\": 6544, \"to\": 6558}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This event should be in the nature of an exhibition\\\".\", \"from\": 6582, \"to\": 6635, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This event\", \"from\": 6582, \"to\": 6592}, {\"ngram\": \"the nature\", \"from\": 6606, \"to\": 6616}, {\"ngram\": \"an exhibition\", \"from\": 6620, \"to\": 6633}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some of the artworks that represented Ireland at the Olympic Games are now in museums and galleries and some are in private collections, but most have been lost due to indifference Furthermore, arts contests were subjective and without the jeopardy of the sports categories.\", \"from\": 6637, \"to\": 6912, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6675, \"end\": 6682, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9999998730172673, \"rank\": 1.2698292772919943e-07, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the artworks\", \"from\": 6645, \"to\": 6657}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games\", \"from\": 6686, \"to\": 6703}, {\"ngram\": \"museums\", \"from\": 6715, \"to\": 6722}, {\"ngram\": \"galleries\", \"from\": 6727, \"to\": 6736}, {\"ngram\": \"private collections\", \"from\": 6753, \"to\": 6772}, {\"ngram\": \"indifference\", \"from\": 6805, \"to\": 6817}, {\"ngram\": \"arts contests\", \"from\": 6831, \"to\": 6844}, {\"ngram\": \"the jeopardy\", \"from\": 6873, \"to\": 6885}, {\"ngram\": \"the sports categories\", \"from\": 6889, \"to\": 6910}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They were also ill-suited for the dawning age of television.\", \"from\": 6913, \"to\": 6973, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the dawning age\", \"from\": 6943, \"to\": 6958}, {\"ngram\": \"television\", \"from\": 6962, \"to\": 6972}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Although the inclusion of the arts competitions demonstrated the importance of culture within the Olympic movement in its early years, the 151 medals awarded in the arts categories wereofficially stricken from the Olympic recordand do not count toward countries' current medal counts.\", \"from\": 6974, \"to\": 7258, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the inclusion\", \"from\": 6983, \"to\": 6996}, {\"ngram\": \"the arts competitions\", \"from\": 7000, \"to\": 7021}, {\"ngram\": \"the importance\", \"from\": 7035, \"to\": 7049}, {\"ngram\": \"culture\", \"from\": 7053, \"to\": 7060}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic movement\", \"from\": 7068, \"to\": 7088}, {\"ngram\": \"its early years\", \"from\": 7092, \"to\": 7107}, {\"ngram\": \"the 151 medals\", \"from\": 7109, \"to\": 7123}, {\"ngram\": \"the arts categories\", \"from\": 7135, \"to\": 7154}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic recordand\", \"from\": 7184, \"to\": 7205}, {\"ngram\": \"countries' current medal counts\", \"from\": 7226, \"to\": 7257}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some of the artworks that represented Ireland at the Olympic Games are now in museums and galleries and some are in private collections, but most have been lost due to indifference.\", \"from\": 7260, \"to\": 7441, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7298, \"end\": 7305, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9999998730172673, \"rank\": 1.2698292772919943e-07, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the artworks\", \"from\": 7268, \"to\": 7280}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games\", \"from\": 7309, \"to\": 7326}, {\"ngram\": \"museums\", \"from\": 7338, \"to\": 7345}, {\"ngram\": \"galleries\", \"from\": 7350, \"to\": 7359}, {\"ngram\": \"private collections\", \"from\": 7376, \"to\": 7395}, {\"ngram\": \"indifference\", \"from\": 7428, \"to\": 7440}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For the Irish entrants, their Olympic success and participation is usually viewed as a quirky fun fact that appears in their biographies.\", \"from\": 7442, \"to\": 7579, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7450, \"end\": 7455, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.7887273727135935, \"rank\": 0.2672969512013196, \"text\": \"Irish\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http: